FBIS3-50235 "dreeu017_c_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC Havel, Polish Defense Chief View `Partnership' LD2501145894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 GMT 25 Jan 94 LD2501145894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] The "Partnership for Peace" was the main topic in the discussion between President Vaclav Havel and Polish Defense Minister Piotr Kolodziejdzyk at Prague Castle today. Both agreed that their countries' attitude toward the U.S. plan for partnership cooperation with NATO was similar. In this context, our president voiced his support for the continuation of mutual consultations and cooperation in modernizing the armies of the two neighboring states. Minister Kolodziejdzyk said that NATO standards should be introduced into these armies as soon as possible and that a joint approach to a safe Europe should be adopted.
